<div class="indented"><a id="comment-7204"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/blood-scales#comment-7204" class="active">My problem...</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Alvin (not verified) on Tue, 2009-02-10 17:00.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>My only problem with this episode was that it was just too quick a resolution for such a great potential storyline.  While Gaeta's turn was recent, a mutiny of Galactica has actually been a long time coming.  Ever since the beginning, Adama's made enemies all over the civilian fleet, and most of them didn't like military-run, fascist-style government (even if it was necessary).  </p>
<p>Personally, I think this mutiny should have been the whole first half of the season, spread out over many episodes.  Imagine the fleet fracturing, characters choosing sides, and then the fight to retake the ship.  Frankly, just a third episode would've helped.  It felt like it ended way too quickly-- like this 2-part story was a distraction, as if the writers just needed something to fill up two episodes.   </p>
<p>I do agree, though, that The Oath is one of the best episodes of the series.</p>
</div>
